body_html:
Now it works.

turns out there is already Apple's own libtool;
⇒ brew uninstall libtool && brew install libtool Uninstalling /usr/local/Cellar/libtool/2.4.6_1... (70 files, 3.7M) ==> Downloading https://homebrew.bintray.com/bottles/libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz Already downloaded: /Users/honghaoli/Library/Caches/Homebrew/libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz ==> Pouring libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz ==> Caveats In order to prevent conflicts with Apple's own libtool we have prepended a "g" so, you have instead: glibtool and glibtoolize. ==> Summary 🍺 /usr/local/Cellar/libtool/2.4.6_1: 70 files, 3.7M

So I have to rename glibtool and glibtoolize back to libtool and libtoolize.

Just post it here in case anyone has the same issue later.

body:
Now it works.

turns out there is already Apple's own `libtool`;
`⇒  brew uninstall libtool && brew install libtool
  Uninstalling /usr/local/Cellar/libtool/2.4.6_1... (70 files, 3.7M)
  ==> Downloading https://homebrew.bintray.com/bottles/libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz
  Already downloaded: /Users/honghaoli/Library/Caches/Homebrew/libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz
  ==> Pouring libtool-2.4.6_1.sierra.bottle.tar.gz
  ==> Caveats
  In order to prevent conflicts with Apple's own libtool we have prepended a "g"
  so, you have instead: glibtool and glibtoolize.
  ==> Summary
  🍺  /usr/local/Cellar/libtool/2.4.6_1: 70 files, 3.7M`

So I have to rename glibtool and glibtoolize back to libtool and libtoolize.

Just post it here in case anyone has the same issue later.
